WEBVTT

1
00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:50.115
- Is it a girl?
- Yes.

2
00:00:50.240 --> 00:00:53.073
- Show me its arm.
- She bears the mark.

3
00:00:53.200 --> 00:00:55.270
No!

4
00:00:57.200 --> 00:01:00.795
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

5
00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.195
- Please help me!
- I can't.

6
00:01:05.320 --> 00:01:07.629
They're going to kill her.

7
00:01:11.760 --> 00:01:14.228
Please! Please!

8
00:01:16.720 --> 00:01:20.076
Oh. thank you. Ethna.
Thank you.

9
00:01:27.720 --> 00:01:30.188
Stand aside for Queen Bavmorda!

10
00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:55.876
You cannot stop the prophecy!

11
00:01:56.000 --> 00:01:58.958
This child will have no power over me.
Start the ritual.

12
00:01:59.080 --> 00:02:01.275
No. No!

13
00:02:01.400 --> 00:02:03.595
Where's the baby?

14
00:02:03.720 --> 00:02:06.075
- The midwife.
- Find that baby. Sorsha.

15
00:02:06.200 --> 00:02:09.397
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

16
00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:11.511
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

17
00:02:11.640 --> 00:02:13.596
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

18
00:02:13.720 --> 00:02:17.076
- My baby will finish you!
- Kill her.

19
00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:37.837
Dada! Dada!

20
00:05:41.120 --> 00:05:43.111
- Dada! Dada!
- Whoa! Whoa!

21
00:05:45.520 --> 00:05:48.557
Dada! Dada!
We found something in the river.

22
00:05:48.680 --> 00:05:50.477
I can't run off and play
with you now. Ranon.

23
00:05:50.600 --> 00:05:52.670
- I've got work to do.
- You gotta come. Hurry!

24
00:05:58.160 --> 00:05:59.912
Come on.

25
00:06:02.680 --> 00:06:05.148
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

26
00:06:05.280 --> 00:06:07.999
But. Dada. it's a baby.

27
00:06:08.120 --> 00:06:12.671
- It's not like us.
- No. It's not a Nelwyn.

28
00:06:12.800 --> 00:06:16.156
- It looks like a Daikini baby.
- What's a Daikini?

29
00:06:16.280 --> 00:06:19.875
Daikinis are big.
Giants who live far away.

30
00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:23.830
She's so cute.

31
00:06:23.960 --> 00:06:26.758
- Can't we keep it. Dada?
- No!

32
00:06:28.280 --> 00:06:32.831
We'll push it downstream
and forget we ever saw it. Come on.

33
00:06:32.960 --> 00:06:34.757
Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!

34
00:06:35.960 --> 00:06:38.838
It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

35
00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:42.157
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

36
00:06:43.760 --> 00:06:48.072
Mr Burglekutt. my husband
hasn't stolen anything!

37
00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:55.913
Ufgood. you still haven't paid
your debts to me.

38
00:06:56.040 --> 00:06:57.996
Where did you get these seeds?

39
00:06:58.120 --> 00:07:00.680
Well. maybe I used magic.

40
00:07:01.840 --> 00:07:04.559
You're no sorcerer. Ufgood.
You're a clown.

41
00:07:04.680 --> 00:07:08.036
I sell the planting seeds around here.
Now tell me where you got them.

42
00:07:08.160 --> 00:07:11.436
My family's been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

43
00:07:11.560 --> 00:07:14.393
There's no law against that.
Mr Burglekutt.

44
00:07:14.520 --> 00:07:17.796
Willow. you didn't leave them
alone by the river?

45
00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:20.395
Magic?

46
00:07:20.520 --> 00:07:23.990
You'll need magic to get your planting
done before the rains start.

47
00:07:26.080 --> 00:07:27.877
I will have this land. Ufgood...

48
00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:31.356
and you're gonna end up
working in the mines.

49
00:07:41.360 --> 00:07:42.918
You're lovely.

50
00:07:43.040 --> 00:07:44.917
Yes. you are.

51
00:07:45.040 --> 00:07:46.473
Kiaya!

52
00:07:47.440 --> 00:07:49.237
Oh. Willow!

53
00:07:49.360 --> 00:07:50.429
Good girl.

54
00:07:50.560 --> 00:07:54.030
Absolutely.
under no condition whatsoever...

55
00:07:54.160 --> 00:07:56.720
is anyone in this family
to fall in love with that baby.

56
00:07:56.840 --> 00:08:01.311
Yes. you are. Come on. Mims.
Come on.

57
00:08:01.440 --> 00:08:03.351
There we are. Come on.

58
00:08:03.480 --> 00:08:06.119
Hey. I will not be ignored!

59
00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:08.675
Mims? Ranon?

60
00:08:20.640 --> 00:08:23.108
You're gonna be all clean.

61
00:08:29.240 --> 00:08:31.754
Willow. do you think we should
take her to the village council?

62
00:08:31.880 --> 00:08:34.269
No. No.
They'll think it's a bad omen.

63
00:08:34.400 --> 00:08:37.073
There'll be a flood or a drought.
and everyone will blame me for it.

64
00:08:37.200 --> 00:08:39.919
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?"

65
00:08:40.040 --> 00:08:42.873
"That's right. And he's that
lousy farmer too. Let's get him!"

66
00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:44.831
Willow. calm down.

67
00:08:44.960 --> 00:08:46.871
Calm down?

68
00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:48.911
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

69
00:08:49.040 --> 00:08:52.555
Love. the High Aldwin hasn't picked
a new apprentice in years.

70
00:08:52.680 --> 00:08:55.717
Tomorrow's gonna be different.
I just know he's gonna pick me.

71
00:08:58.480 --> 00:09:01.916
- Here. Hold her.
- Hey. no. I don't want her. Kiaya.

72
00:09:02.040 --> 00:09:04.679
Hold her while I get some milk.

73
00:09:12.040 --> 00:09:14.429
Dada. she likes you.

74
00:09:23.600 --> 00:09:25.158
Bye.

75
00:09:26.640 --> 00:09:28.676
Come on. kids. Let's go.

76
00:09:35.800 --> 00:09:39.236
I will now magically join the rings!

77
00:10:07.120 --> 00:10:08.473
Thank you. son.

78
00:10:09.800 --> 00:10:13.395
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

79
00:10:29.160 --> 00:10:31.230
Give me a ripe one. Good.

80
00:10:37.320 --> 00:10:41.313
And now.
for my final amazing feat...

81
00:10:41.440 --> 00:10:45.592
I will make
this entire pig disappear!

82
00:10:55.720 --> 00:10:58.951
Please watch very closely.

83
00:10:59.080 --> 00:11:02.709
<i>Wuppity bairn. deru. deru!</i>

84
00:11:08.080 --> 00:11:10.071
What happened to your pig?

85
00:11:11.520 --> 00:11:14.353
No!
Hey. come here. you!

86
00:11:18.720 --> 00:11:20.676
I seen enough.

87
00:11:36.480 --> 00:11:37.799
Attention!

88
00:11:38.480 --> 00:11:42.439
The High Aldwin will now make his choice
for his new apprentice!

89
00:11:42.560 --> 00:11:45.836
Bring forth the hopefuls.

90
00:11:45.960 --> 00:11:48.190
- Good luck.
- Good luck. Dada.

91
00:11:48.320 --> 00:11:51.869
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

92
00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:54.355
Is this a joke?

93
00:12:02.040 --> 00:12:06.272
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

94
00:12:06.880 --> 00:12:10.714
Forget all you know
or think you know.

95
00:12:10.840 --> 00:12:14.628
All that you require
is your intuition.

96
00:12:14.760 --> 00:12:18.673
Now. the power
to control the world...

97
00:12:18.800 --> 00:12:21.917
is in which finger?

98
00:13:04.200 --> 00:13:06.589
No apprentice this year!

99
00:13:27.280 --> 00:13:30.477
- Where's Mims?
- I don't know. She was right here!

100
00:13:30.600 --> 00:13:33.319
Take Ranon in there. quick!

101
00:13:40.960 --> 00:13:42.518
Mims!

102
00:14:00.920 --> 00:14:02.592
I'm scared. Dada!

103
00:14:13.720 --> 00:14:16.154
Come on!

104
00:14:33.160 --> 00:14:34.912
Vohnkar!

105
00:14:45.120 --> 00:14:47.873
- Check to make sure.
- It's dead!

106
00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:51.832
Dada! Dada!

107
00:14:55.080 --> 00:14:57.196
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

108
00:15:00.800 --> 00:15:03.678
- Mommy.
- Kiaya!

109
00:15:15.240 --> 00:15:16.992
I'm here.

110
00:15:24.600 --> 00:15:26.556
We can't keep the baby. Kiaya.

111
00:15:26.680 --> 00:15:29.319
We have to take her
to the village council.

112
00:15:42.280 --> 00:15:43.838
Silence!

113
00:15:43.960 --> 00:15:47.032
One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

114
00:15:47.160 --> 00:15:49.276
And you can be assured
that they won't give up...

115
00:15:49.400 --> 00:15:51.356
until they find
what they're looking for!

116
00:15:51.480 --> 00:15:54.552
- It's a sign!
- Who's to blame for this?

117
00:15:54.680 --> 00:15:56.989
We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!

118
00:15:59.240 --> 00:16:01.708
In the pit! In the pit!

119
00:16:06.640 --> 00:16:08.596
Willow.

120
00:16:08.720 --> 00:16:10.153
Willow Ufgood.

121
00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:14.038
Come forward.

122
00:16:20.320 --> 00:16:24.472
My children found this baby
alone by the river. High Aldwin.

123
00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:31.991
A Daikini child.

124
00:16:32.160 --> 00:16:34.958
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

125
00:16:36.440 --> 00:16:39.512
- They'll kill her! You can't!
- It isn't one of us.

126
00:16:39.640 --> 00:16:42.154
This child is special!

127
00:16:43.040 --> 00:16:46.350
This child must be taken
beyond the boundaries of our village.

128
00:16:46.480 --> 00:16:49.358
All the way across
the great river...

129
00:16:49.480 --> 00:16:51.436
to the Daikini crossroads.

130
00:16:51.560 --> 00:16:53.869
Well. who'll do that?

131
00:16:54.400 --> 00:16:56.675
It seems only fair...

132
00:16:56.800 --> 00:16:59.155
that the man to take
this baby to the crossroads...

133
00:16:59.280 --> 00:17:02.158
be the very man
who plucked it out of the river.

134
00:17:03.800 --> 00:17:06.234
I nominate Willow Ufgood.

135
00:17:06.360 --> 00:17:07.475
No!

136
00:17:08.880 --> 00:17:11.189
I will consult the bones!

137
00:17:19.840 --> 00:17:22.718
The bones tell me nothing.

138
00:17:27.720 --> 00:17:29.870
Do you have any love
for this child?

139
00:17:38.360 --> 00:17:39.713
Yes.

140
00:17:40.960 --> 00:17:42.313
Yes. I do.

141
00:17:42.440 --> 00:17:45.318
The bones have spoken!

142
00:17:46.720 --> 00:17:50.474
Willow Ufgood. the safety
of this village depends upon you.

143
00:17:50.600 --> 00:17:54.479
- Praise the bones!
- Praise the bones!

144
00:17:54.600 --> 00:17:56.955
But you will need help.

145
00:17:57.080 --> 00:18:02.074
Who has the courage to protect
our brave fellow on his journey?

146
00:18:04.520 --> 00:18:08.035
- I'll go with him.
- Ah. Meegosh.

147
00:18:08.160 --> 00:18:09.513
Excellent choice.

148
00:18:10.280 --> 00:18:13.716
- I'll go!
- Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

149
00:18:13.840 --> 00:18:16.354
No! Not Vohnkar!
He's the best warrior in the village!

150
00:18:16.480 --> 00:18:19.438
We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!

151
00:18:26.800 --> 00:18:29.678
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

152
00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:34.879
And according to the bones.
that leader is...

153
00:18:35.960 --> 00:18:37.712
you. Burglekutt!

154
00:18:39.520 --> 00:18:41.238
Vohnkar!

155
00:18:42.280 --> 00:18:46.159
- What's your problem. son?
- How do you mean?

156
00:18:46.880 --> 00:18:51.317
When I held up my fingers.
what was your first impulse?

157
00:18:51.440 --> 00:18:54.352
- Well. it was stupid.
- Just tell me.

158
00:18:55.240 --> 00:18:57.708
- To pick my own finger.
- Aha!

159
00:18:57.840 --> 00:19:01.276
That was the correct answer.
You lack faith in yourself.

160
00:19:01.400 --> 00:19:04.073
More than anyone in the village...

161
00:19:04.200 --> 00:19:06.668
you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.

162
00:19:06.800 --> 00:19:11.316
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

163
00:19:13.040 --> 00:19:15.315
These will protect you.

164
00:19:15.440 --> 00:19:18.079
- Acorns?
- They're magic!

165
00:19:18.200 --> 00:19:21.909
Anything you throw them at
turns to stone.

166
00:19:24.960 --> 00:19:28.032
You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.

167
00:19:40.480 --> 00:19:42.118
Are you scared. Dada?

168
00:19:43.600 --> 00:19:44.715
No.

169
00:19:44.840 --> 00:19:46.796
Even with fairies in the woods...

170
00:19:46.920 --> 00:19:48.797
that'll put you to sleep
for a hundred years?

171
00:19:50.360 --> 00:19:52.794
- Doesn't bother me.
- Brownies?

172
00:19:52.920 --> 00:19:55.673
- Dragons?
- Trolls?

173
00:19:55.800 --> 00:19:59.031
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

174
00:19:59.200 --> 00:20:02.590
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

175
00:20:02.720 --> 00:20:05.075
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

176
00:20:05.200 --> 00:20:07.316
Me too. Me too. Dada.

177
00:20:08.840 --> 00:20:11.070
What a lucky father I am.

178
00:20:11.200 --> 00:20:13.839
I wish I could take
you bobbins with me.

179
00:20:16.920 --> 00:20:18.956
Goodbye. Dada.

180
00:20:21.480 --> 00:20:23.516
Go play! Go on.

181
00:20:28.800 --> 00:20:31.553
We've never been apart.

182
00:20:34.280 --> 00:20:36.430
I miss you already.

183
00:20:37.320 --> 00:20:39.072
Don't worry. Kiaya.

184
00:20:39.200 --> 00:20:42.909
I'll be fine. and I'll be back
before you know it.

185
00:20:45.200 --> 00:20:47.760
Well. remember to keep her warm.

186
00:20:49.760 --> 00:20:52.274
And here.

187
00:20:54.440 --> 00:20:57.079
This will bring you luck.

188
00:21:10.440 --> 00:21:12.829
Good brave people!

189
00:21:13.760 --> 00:21:16.320
The outer world is
no place for a Nelwyn.

190
00:21:16.440 --> 00:21:18.954
Give the baby
to the first Daikini you see...

191
00:21:19.080 --> 00:21:21.116
then hurry home.

192
00:21:24.360 --> 00:21:27.750
<i>Tuatha lawkathok tuatha!</i>

193
00:21:28.600 --> 00:21:31.194
Go in the direction
the bird is flying!

194
00:21:35.720 --> 00:21:37.790
It's going back to the village!

195
00:21:39.400 --> 00:21:41.516
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

196
00:21:41.640 --> 00:21:43.596
Move out!

197
00:22:06.760 --> 00:22:09.513
- Hold on. Meegosh.
- What's wrong?

198
00:22:10.160 --> 00:22:12.276
We have to stop.

199
00:22:12.400 --> 00:22:13.958
Stop? Why?

200
00:22:14.080 --> 00:22:16.310
The baby's sick.

201
00:22:20.800 --> 00:22:23.234
She's not sick!
Let me see.

202
00:22:27.080 --> 00:22:29.036
Take her! Take her!

203
00:22:30.320 --> 00:22:33.198
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

204
00:22:36.440 --> 00:22:37.998
Clean me up.

205
00:22:41.160 --> 00:22:43.674
I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

206
00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:47.156
- Sorsha. you're useless!
- I'm backtracking the nursemaid's trail.

207
00:22:47.280 --> 00:22:49.669
I'll find where she hid the baby.

208
00:22:51.600 --> 00:22:53.716
Ah. General Kael. at last.

209
00:22:54.680 --> 00:22:58.309
My queen. I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

210
00:22:58.440 --> 00:23:01.910
Well done. But now I have
another task for you.

211
00:23:02.040 --> 00:23:07.239
Help my daughter to find
that tiny. helpless baby...

212
00:23:07.360 --> 00:23:09.157
that continues somehow
to elude her.

213
00:23:11.120 --> 00:23:14.078
The baby of the prophecy?
The one that would destroy you?

214
00:23:14.200 --> 00:23:16.316
I need that baby alive.

215
00:23:16.440 --> 00:23:18.715
I must perform
the ritual that will exile...

216
00:23:18.840 --> 00:23:22.037
the child's spirit into oblivion.

217
00:23:22.160 --> 00:23:24.720
- Find her!
- I don't need his help. Mother.

218
00:23:24.840 --> 00:23:26.717
You'll do as I say. child.

219
00:23:33.000 --> 00:23:35.036
I read the signs.

220
00:23:35.160 --> 00:23:38.152
One day. I fear.
your daughter will betray you.

221
00:23:38.280 --> 00:23:42.239
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

222
00:23:57.800 --> 00:23:59.552
Move!

223
00:24:00.280 --> 00:24:03.158
It's an ambush.
Come on. Move!

224
00:24:05.880 --> 00:24:07.438
Come on!

225
00:24:18.640 --> 00:24:20.437
The Nelwyns have got the baby.

226
00:24:20.560 --> 00:24:23.120
We've searched the village. but a group
of them are on the road somewhere.

227
00:24:23.240 --> 00:24:26.118
They couldn't have gone far!

228
00:24:26.240 --> 00:24:28.310
Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

229
00:24:36.200 --> 00:24:38.270
Come.
We'll keep to the woods.

230
00:25:16.200 --> 00:25:17.633
That's it!

231
00:25:17.760 --> 00:25:19.716
It's the crossroads!

232
00:25:36.440 --> 00:25:39.591
Keep this fire high.
We don't know what's out there.

233
00:25:45.360 --> 00:25:47.430
What was that?

234
00:25:48.520 --> 00:25:50.158
Get the spears!

235
00:26:08.000 --> 00:26:11.595
Give me some water. peck.
or you die.

236
00:26:11.720 --> 00:26:13.995
Do you understand?

237
00:26:14.120 --> 00:26:15.872
Water.

238
00:26:18.440 --> 00:26:19.793
Hurry up!

239
00:26:23.760 --> 00:26:26.479
Get me some water.
you measly little pecks!

240
00:26:27.840 --> 00:26:29.876
It's a Daikini. We're in luck.

241
00:26:30.960 --> 00:26:33.872
- We can't give her to him!
- Somebody put him there for a reason.

242
00:26:34.000 --> 00:26:38.073
Ufgood. we've got to get rid of her.
Those soldiers are after us.

243
00:26:38.840 --> 00:26:41.479
He's looking right at us.

244
00:26:45.280 --> 00:26:47.191
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

245
00:26:47.920 --> 00:26:49.990
I'm somebody.

246
00:26:50.760 --> 00:26:53.672
Let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby.

247
00:26:56.080 --> 00:26:58.275
I trust him completely.

248
00:26:58.400 --> 00:27:01.995
- But he tried to strangle me!
- I want to go home.

249
00:27:02.120 --> 00:27:05.556
No. Burglekutt!
We should wait!

250
00:27:05.680 --> 00:27:07.557
Are you challenging my authority?

251
00:27:07.680 --> 00:27:10.831
As far as this baby
is concerned. yes.

252
00:27:10.960 --> 00:27:13.838
Don't listen to him. Burglekutt.

253
00:27:15.080 --> 00:27:18.789
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

254
00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:22.673
That's a bad idea. Very bad.
Dangerous out there.

255
00:27:22.800 --> 00:27:26.634
- Get the gear. men.
- Vohnkar...

256
00:27:26.760 --> 00:27:31.675
- It's not his decision!
- Burglekutt. you're troll dung.

257
00:27:31.800 --> 00:27:35.429
- Don't let him talk to you that way.
- Listen here. runt.

258
00:27:35.560 --> 00:27:39.155
While you're wasting your time here.
your fields aren't getting planted.

259
00:27:39.280 --> 00:27:41.032
Think about it!

260
00:27:41.160 --> 00:27:45.119
- Burglekutt. I'm gonna...
- You're gonna what?

261
00:27:50.320 --> 00:27:53.039
Someday. Burglekutt.
Someday.

262
00:27:53.160 --> 00:27:54.991
Vohnkar. let's go!

263
00:27:58.400 --> 00:28:01.198
Meegosh. are you coming?

264
00:28:03.400 --> 00:28:04.958
I'm staying.

265
00:28:05.080 --> 00:28:06.798
Come on. men.

266
00:28:06.920 --> 00:28:10.879
Burglekutt. let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby. I swear.

267
00:28:11.680 --> 00:28:13.636
Just let me out of here.
Please!

268
00:28:13.760 --> 00:28:16.911
Vohnkar. let me borrow that spear
just for a minute.

269
00:28:17.040 --> 00:28:19.156
Well. at least get me some water!

270
00:28:19.280 --> 00:28:22.078
Burglekutt. don't leave me alone
with these two!

271
00:28:26.400 --> 00:28:28.630
What'll we do now. Willow?

272
00:28:28.760 --> 00:28:31.228
Well. that was really stupid. peck.

273
00:28:31.360 --> 00:28:35.911
- Don't call me a peck.
- Oh. I'm sorry. peck.

274
00:28:36.040 --> 00:28:39.589
- Peck. peck. peck. peck.
- You be careful!

275
00:28:40.480 --> 00:28:43.199
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

276
00:28:44.680 --> 00:28:47.274
I'll throw it at you
and turn you to stone.

277
00:28:49.080 --> 00:28:50.877
I'm really scared.

278
00:28:51.040 --> 00:28:53.395
No. don't! Don't!

279
00:28:53.520 --> 00:28:56.478
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

280
00:28:57.320 --> 00:28:59.117
I wouldn't want to waste it!

281
00:29:01.080 --> 00:29:04.834
Peck. peck. peck. peck!

282
00:29:33.080 --> 00:29:34.991
What was that?

283
00:29:38.360 --> 00:29:40.715
Mornin'. boys.

284
00:29:41.960 --> 00:29:44.918
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

285
00:29:46.000 --> 00:29:49.151
I don't think
I introduced myself yesterday.

286
00:29:49.280 --> 00:29:52.556
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh...

287
00:29:52.680 --> 00:29:54.636
No. Meegosh.

288
00:29:54.760 --> 00:29:56.955
Don't go near him.
He's dangerous.

289
00:29:57.080 --> 00:29:58.832
I am not.

290
00:29:59.920 --> 00:30:01.911
Good.

291
00:30:05.560 --> 00:30:07.676
Stop! Wait!

292
00:30:18.080 --> 00:30:20.640
- What's going on?
- Smells like a battle.

293
00:30:22.200 --> 00:30:24.111
I suppose you're a warrior.

294
00:30:24.240 --> 00:30:26.595
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

295
00:30:29.480 --> 00:30:32.950
Say. could I have
some of that water?

296
00:30:42.400 --> 00:30:44.595
I don't know why I try.

297
00:30:52.040 --> 00:30:54.634
I guess I am gonna die here.
Who cares?

298
00:30:54.760 --> 00:30:56.557
- Here.
- Thanks. friend.

299
00:30:58.280 --> 00:31:00.077
What's that?

300
00:31:00.200 --> 00:31:02.794
I'd say
two or three hundred horses...

301
00:31:02.920 --> 00:31:06.674
five or six wagons.
and about a thousand fools.

302
00:31:10.640 --> 00:31:12.915
- Thank you.
- Come on. Meegosh.

303
00:31:18.480 --> 00:31:20.675
It's gonna be all right.
little bobbin.

304
00:31:28.360 --> 00:31:30.112
Everything's gonna be all right.

305
00:31:33.400 --> 00:31:36.233
- Excuse me. sir.
- Out of the way. peck!

306
00:31:39.200 --> 00:31:41.191
Pardon me.

307
00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:49.638
Excuse me. sir.

308
00:31:50.800 --> 00:31:52.950
We found one of your babies
in our village.

309
00:31:53.080 --> 00:31:55.799
Will you please take care of her?

310
00:31:56.840 --> 00:32:00.037
We're going into battle. little ones.
Find a woman to take care of her.

311
00:32:01.200 --> 00:32:03.555
They thought you were
a woman. Airk.

312
00:32:04.640 --> 00:32:06.870
Well...

313
00:32:07.000 --> 00:32:09.389
Madmartigan!
What did you do this time?

314
00:32:09.520 --> 00:32:11.351
Nothing you wouldn't have done
in my place.

315
00:32:11.480 --> 00:32:13.869
I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.

316
00:32:14.000 --> 00:32:17.037
At least I'm not herding sheep.
What are you doing this far north?

317
00:32:17.160 --> 00:32:19.958
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

318
00:32:20.080 --> 00:32:21.638
The castle?

319
00:32:21.760 --> 00:32:23.671
Bavmorda's troops are crushing
everything in sight.

320
00:32:23.800 --> 00:32:25.597
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

321
00:32:25.720 --> 00:32:27.790
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

322
00:32:27.920 --> 00:32:32.118
Madmartigan.
I still serve Galladoorn.

323
00:32:32.240 --> 00:32:34.071
You serve no one.

324
00:32:34.200 --> 00:32:36.316
Remember?

325
00:32:36.440 --> 00:32:38.396
Sit in your coffin and rot.

326
00:32:39.600 --> 00:32:42.478
Wait. Airk. You need me!

327
00:32:42.600 --> 00:32:44.875
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

328
00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:47.468
When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off...

329
00:32:47.600 --> 00:32:49.556
and stick it on a pig pole!

330
00:33:08.360 --> 00:33:10.794
I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

331
00:33:15.120 --> 00:33:17.076
We're running out of food.

332
00:33:19.800 --> 00:33:21.916
Nobody's gonna
take care of that baby.

333
00:33:22.040 --> 00:33:24.759
You know why?
Nobody cares.

334
00:33:27.680 --> 00:33:29.636
Except me.

335
00:33:30.760 --> 00:33:35.117
You want to go back to your families.
I want out of this cage.

336
00:33:35.240 --> 00:33:38.994
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her like she was my own.

337
00:33:39.120 --> 00:33:41.918
I believe he would. Willow.

338
00:33:42.040 --> 00:33:44.429
He doesn't know anything
about babies.

339
00:33:45.400 --> 00:33:49.518
Right. but I know
a lot of women who do.

340
00:33:50.400 --> 00:33:52.391
If I had somebody in my life...

341
00:33:53.320 --> 00:33:55.914
a little daughter. perhaps...

342
00:33:56.040 --> 00:33:59.077
I might have a reason
to go on living.

343
00:34:02.280 --> 00:34:05.272
You can't leave me
in here to die.

344
00:34:05.400 --> 00:34:07.914
Not when all I want to do
is protect her.

345
00:34:20.760 --> 00:34:24.435
I feel better!

346
00:34:24.560 --> 00:34:28.075
- You've done the right thing!
- Okay. All right.

347
00:34:28.200 --> 00:34:30.031
You gotta promise to feed her.

348
00:34:30.160 --> 00:34:32.435
Come to Daddy. little darlin'.

349
00:34:32.560 --> 00:34:35.597
- And keep her clean.
- Absolutely.

350
00:34:45.560 --> 00:34:47.312
She likes me.

351
00:34:49.360 --> 00:34:51.590
Here are her changing rags.

352
00:34:51.720 --> 00:34:53.756
- And her milk bladder.
- Any milk in there?

353
00:34:53.920 --> 00:34:57.879
- It's for her!
- I wouldn't steal from a baby.

354
00:35:00.720 --> 00:35:02.995
You worry too much. peck.

355
00:35:03.120 --> 00:35:06.112
- It's Willow.
- I mean Willow.

356
00:35:07.440 --> 00:35:10.238
Now listen. boys... Willow.

357
00:35:10.360 --> 00:35:12.430
You've done the right thing.

358
00:35:12.560 --> 00:35:15.677
Now I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

359
00:35:21.600 --> 00:35:23.830
Goodbye. little one.

360
00:35:34.560 --> 00:35:36.516
Please take good care of her.

361
00:35:38.800 --> 00:35:40.995
I give you my word of honour!

362
00:35:48.040 --> 00:35:51.191
- Meegosh. slow down!
- Oh. come on!

363
00:35:51.320 --> 00:35:53.675
If we hurry. we could be home
by tomorrow morning.

364
00:35:53.800 --> 00:35:56.360
We'll be heroes.

365
00:35:56.480 --> 00:35:58.755
- Do you really think so?
- Sure.

366
00:35:58.880 --> 00:36:00.996
"Look. there's Willow and Meegosh.

367
00:36:01.120 --> 00:36:03.236
The heroes have come home."

368
00:36:03.360 --> 00:36:06.238
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

369
00:36:06.360 --> 00:36:08.555
Yeah. medals!

370
00:36:15.960 --> 00:36:18.269
Did we do the right thing?

371
00:36:18.400 --> 00:36:21.119
Absolutely.
There's nothing to worry about.

372
00:36:29.200 --> 00:36:34.149
I stole the baby! I stole the baby!

373
00:36:36.600 --> 00:36:39.797
That's my baby!
Stop! Wait! Come back!

374
00:36:39.920 --> 00:36:42.832
Left. you stupid bird. Left!

375
00:36:49.240 --> 00:36:51.435
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

376
00:36:52.480 --> 00:36:55.517
Come on. Meegosh!

377
00:37:01.440 --> 00:37:03.396
We'll outrun 'em!

378
00:37:07.960 --> 00:37:09.916
Hey. ugly. wake up!

379
00:37:17.280 --> 00:37:19.350
Stand your ground.
These are our prisoners.

380
00:37:19.480 --> 00:37:22.119
Meegosh. where's the baby?

381
00:37:22.240 --> 00:37:25.277
<i>- Bring the Nelwyns to me.</i>
- All right. you heard her!

382
00:37:25.400 --> 00:37:28.949
- What's going on?
- Shut up. or I'll break your nose.

383
00:37:29.080 --> 00:37:31.310
You are mine to toy with.

384
00:37:32.360 --> 00:37:34.749
Forward!

385
00:37:35.800 --> 00:37:37.631
Get the rope.

386
00:37:40.080 --> 00:37:44.631
Where did you get that baby?

387
00:37:44.760 --> 00:37:48.116
I stole it from a stupid Daikini.

388
00:37:50.600 --> 00:37:55.037
<i>Franjean. release the Nelwyns.</i>
<i>and stop pestering them.</i>

389
00:38:11.240 --> 00:38:13.196
<i>Welcome to my kingdom.</i>

390
00:38:20.840 --> 00:38:25.118
- I'm happy to meet you. Willow Ufgood.
- How do you know my name?

391
00:38:25.880 --> 00:38:28.314
Elora Danan told me.

392
00:38:28.440 --> 00:38:31.477
Elora?
Elora. Willow is here.

393
00:38:35.120 --> 00:38:39.557
- But she's just a baby.
- She's very special.

394
00:38:39.680 --> 00:38:43.912
My Brownies have been searching for her
ever since we heard she was born.

395
00:38:45.680 --> 00:38:49.559
Elora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

396
00:38:49.680 --> 00:38:51.079
Me?

397
00:38:51.200 --> 00:38:54.476
Yes. She likes you.

398
00:38:55.600 --> 00:39:00.310
And Elora Danan knows
you have the courage to help us.

399
00:39:00.440 --> 00:39:03.830
Take my wand
to the sorceress Fin Raziel.

400
00:39:03.960 --> 00:39:07.999
She will guide you and Elora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen...

401
00:39:08.120 --> 00:39:11.032
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

402
00:39:11.160 --> 00:39:14.675
You need a warrior
for a job like this. I'm a nobody.

403
00:39:14.800 --> 00:39:17.997
Elora. you don't want me.

404
00:39:18.120 --> 00:39:21.590
Tell her.
I'm short. even for a Nelwyn.

405
00:39:25.720 --> 00:39:27.676
Hello?

406
00:39:34.080 --> 00:39:37.277
Elora Danan must survive!

407
00:39:37.400 --> 00:39:39.356
She must fulfil her destiny...

408
00:39:39.480 --> 00:39:42.040
and bring about the downfall
of Queen Bavmorda...

409
00:39:42.160 --> 00:39:44.799
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

410
00:39:44.920 --> 00:39:49.072
Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control the lives...

411
00:39:49.200 --> 00:39:53.159
of your village.
your children... everyone.

412
00:39:58.040 --> 00:40:01.350
All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.

413
00:40:02.680 --> 00:40:05.069
The choice is yours.

414
00:40:28.680 --> 00:40:31.797
Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.

415
00:40:32.680 --> 00:40:35.592
- It's time to go home.
- Home?

416
00:40:39.440 --> 00:40:41.396
Listen. Meegosh.

417
00:40:41.520 --> 00:40:44.830
Tell Kiaya I love her
and I think of her every day.

418
00:40:47.320 --> 00:40:49.993
And tell her I'm not going to let
anything happen to the baby.

419
00:40:50.120 --> 00:40:52.588
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

420
00:40:53.920 --> 00:40:55.478
I hope so.

421
00:40:56.920 --> 00:40:58.911
Listen. be careful.

422
00:41:05.600 --> 00:41:09.036
- I know the way. Franjean.
- You always think you know the way.

423
00:41:09.160 --> 00:41:10.912
I am the leader!

424
00:41:11.040 --> 00:41:13.554
- How long will it take to find Raziel?
- Not long.

425
00:41:13.680 --> 00:41:16.877
She's been exiled to an island
just over those hills.

426
00:41:17.000 --> 00:41:19.753
- She's what?
- Exiled.

427
00:41:19.880 --> 00:41:22.838
By the evil Queen Bavmorda.

428
00:41:23.880 --> 00:41:26.348
Rool. you fool. He does not need
to know everything!

429
00:41:26.480 --> 00:41:28.914
- I didn't tell him everything.
- You told him enough.

430
00:41:29.040 --> 00:41:32.157
You mentioned the island.
you mentioned the queen.

431
00:41:32.520 --> 00:41:33.794
So?

432
00:41:33.920 --> 00:41:36.559
What do you mean? What are
you saying. mysterious island?

433
00:41:36.680 --> 00:41:39.148
Don't play with that wand.

434
00:41:39.280 --> 00:41:41.669
Cherlindrea told you
it holds vast powers.

435
00:41:41.800 --> 00:41:46.828
Only a great sorcerer can use it.
not a stupid peck like you.

436
00:41:46.960 --> 00:41:49.918
- This way.
- No. No. No. I don't think so.

437
00:41:50.040 --> 00:41:52.190
- All right. then this way.
- Nope.

438
00:41:52.320 --> 00:41:54.709
- This way.
- This way?

439
00:41:54.840 --> 00:41:58.355
- That's what I said.
- This way.

440
00:41:58.480 --> 00:42:00.311
Are you sure you know
where you're going?

441
00:42:00.440 --> 00:42:04.399
Of course. With us as your guides.
no harm will befall you.

442
00:42:20.520 --> 00:42:22.431
We are not going in there!

443
00:42:22.560 --> 00:42:25.358
But Elora needs fresh milk.
and we're drenched.

444
00:42:25.480 --> 00:42:28.631
You are not in command
here. shorty. I am!

445
00:42:28.760 --> 00:42:30.716
You hear me?

446
00:43:08.440 --> 00:43:10.715
Excuse me? Excuse me.

447
00:43:10.840 --> 00:43:13.638
Could you spare some milk
for this poor. hungry baby?

448
00:43:13.760 --> 00:43:15.478
Get out of here. peck!

449
00:43:15.600 --> 00:43:18.273
Get outta here or we'll cook ya!

450
00:43:32.200 --> 00:43:34.395
Look at her!

451
00:43:34.520 --> 00:43:36.636
I could use a love potion on her!

452
00:43:36.760 --> 00:43:40.389
Franjean! Give me
that dust of broken heart.

453
00:43:40.520 --> 00:43:42.112
Come on! Give it to me!

454
00:43:42.240 --> 00:43:45.391
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

455
00:43:49.360 --> 00:43:51.351
Hey. quiet!
You want to get us killed?

456
00:43:58.080 --> 00:44:02.596
Oh. Rool! Always playing
with those fairy love potions.

457
00:44:06.120 --> 00:44:08.395
You are so beautiful!

458
00:44:09.920 --> 00:44:12.309
Your eyes!
Your whiskers!

459
00:44:12.440 --> 00:44:16.672
- I have to kiss you!
- Rool! That dust of broken heart!

460
00:44:31.000 --> 00:44:32.752
Beer!

461
00:44:36.080 --> 00:44:38.036
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

462
00:44:42.480 --> 00:44:46.234
Hurry! Hurry!
My husband's coming!

463
00:44:46.360 --> 00:44:48.271
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

464
00:44:48.400 --> 00:44:50.868
- How do I look?
- Not you!

465
00:44:52.080 --> 00:44:53.877
Where the hell did you come from?

466
00:44:54.000 --> 00:44:56.116
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

467
00:44:56.240 --> 00:44:57.673
Don't I know you?

468
00:44:57.800 --> 00:45:01.270
I stole the baby from you. Daikini.
while you were taking a pee-pee!

469
00:45:01.400 --> 00:45:04.312
- Cover your face!
- You are crawling with Brownies.

470
00:45:04.600 --> 00:45:07.034
I hate Brownies!

471
00:45:08.760 --> 00:45:10.910
- Where is he?
- Hello. dear.

472
00:45:11.040 --> 00:45:13.270
There's nobody here
but me and. uh. my...

473
00:45:13.400 --> 00:45:15.630
- I'll kill him!
- My cousin. Hilda.

474
00:45:15.760 --> 00:45:17.876
Hilda?

475
00:45:18.000 --> 00:45:20.594
Hilda. this is my husband. Llug.

476
00:45:20.720 --> 00:45:22.711
Big husband.
How do you do?

477
00:45:27.000 --> 00:45:30.993
- Come on. girly. Don't be shy.
- Give her back!

478
00:45:31.720 --> 00:45:33.950
- Pecks make such terrible nursemaids.
- Nursemaid?

479
00:45:34.080 --> 00:45:36.036
They get too excited.

480
00:45:36.920 --> 00:45:39.388
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

481
00:45:43.000 --> 00:45:44.797
Stop. please.

482
00:45:46.080 --> 00:45:48.913
Come on.
Fight like a man!

483
00:45:49.040 --> 00:45:50.792
Want to breed?

484
00:45:50.920 --> 00:45:53.753
Tempting. but no.

485
00:45:57.000 --> 00:45:59.468
- Thank you. Time to leave.
- Bye. Hilda!

486
00:45:59.600 --> 00:46:01.591
Take them out!

487
00:46:02.720 --> 00:46:05.996
Come along! Move along!

488
00:46:06.120 --> 00:46:08.680
Gather up all these babies.

489
00:46:08.800 --> 00:46:10.950
That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.

490
00:46:14.560 --> 00:46:16.551
That's not the one.

491
00:46:20.160 --> 00:46:22.754
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

492
00:46:22.880 --> 00:46:25.314
- Yes. I am.
- Let me see it.

493
00:46:25.440 --> 00:46:26.919
No! Don't let her!

494
00:46:28.520 --> 00:46:31.193
I gave you an order. woman!

495
00:46:41.920 --> 00:46:43.512
You're beautiful!

496
00:46:43.640 --> 00:46:46.791
- And you're very strong.
- Thank you.

497
00:46:49.680 --> 00:46:52.592
You're no woman!

498
00:46:52.720 --> 00:46:54.472
- Not a woman?
- Gentlemen...

499
00:46:54.600 --> 00:46:56.318
Not a woman?

500
00:46:56.440 --> 00:46:58.032
Meet Llug.

501
00:47:00.360 --> 00:47:02.271
- After them!
- Out of the way!

502
00:47:08.360 --> 00:47:09.475
To the horses!

503
00:47:21.560 --> 00:47:25.235
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

504
00:47:28.640 --> 00:47:30.949
He's not a woman!

505
00:47:37.280 --> 00:47:40.511
Madmartigan. stop!

506
00:47:58.760 --> 00:48:01.115
Madmartigan. I'm warning you...

507
00:48:04.320 --> 00:48:06.595
Prepare to die!

508
00:48:29.080 --> 00:48:31.275
Madmartigan! Stop!

509
00:48:46.680 --> 00:48:49.672
No more beer.

510
00:49:00.160 --> 00:49:02.071
Franjean. help me!

511
00:49:06.560 --> 00:49:09.313
- Rool! Rool!
- Help!

512
00:49:12.800 --> 00:49:16.110
- Rool! What are you doing?
- Help me!

513
00:49:21.320 --> 00:49:23.436
- Come on.
- Pull me in.

514
00:49:59.080 --> 00:50:02.436
Rool. this isn't funny!
Help me cut the rope!

515
00:50:38.400 --> 00:50:40.834
Willow. stay down!

516
00:50:44.440 --> 00:50:46.351
Whoa!

517
00:50:48.720 --> 00:50:50.472
Have you gone crazy?

518
00:50:50.600 --> 00:50:52.591
You can't chase around
with Elora like this.

519
00:50:52.720 --> 00:50:54.995
We're getting off!

520
00:51:27.280 --> 00:51:29.748
Now we stop. peck.

521
00:51:30.880 --> 00:51:33.235
Stupid Daikini!

522
00:51:33.360 --> 00:51:35.920
Ask him to stop the wagon.

523
00:51:36.040 --> 00:51:39.999
Madmartigan! You never. ever
drive that fast with an infant!

524
00:51:41.720 --> 00:51:43.836
I just saved that infant's life!

525
00:51:47.640 --> 00:51:49.437
Gather your wits. Come on.

526
00:51:49.560 --> 00:51:52.393
- Don't worry about me. I'm fine!
- Come on!

527
00:51:54.320 --> 00:51:55.514
Get down!

528
00:51:55.640 --> 00:51:57.870
Where am I?

529
00:51:59.760 --> 00:52:01.716
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

530
00:52:18.760 --> 00:52:21.479
You better clear out. Willow.
before those troops come back.

531
00:52:21.600 --> 00:52:24.876
- My head!
- We don't need him. Elora.

532
00:52:32.960 --> 00:52:34.916
Madmartigan. wait!

533
00:52:35.040 --> 00:52:38.191
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

534
00:52:38.320 --> 00:52:40.151
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

535
00:52:40.280 --> 00:52:43.317
My help?
What do you need my help for?

536
00:52:43.440 --> 00:52:45.431
You're a sorcerer!

537
00:52:45.560 --> 00:52:48.632
You're a great warrior
and a swordsman.

538
00:52:48.760 --> 00:52:51.479
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

539
00:52:52.600 --> 00:52:55.637
Are you trying to make my life
more difficult than it already is?

540
00:53:00.040 --> 00:53:02.508
Hurry! Big dogs!

541
00:53:02.640 --> 00:53:06.633
Look. I'm sorry I got angry.

542
00:53:06.760 --> 00:53:08.591
We wouldn't have escaped
without you.

543
00:53:22.240 --> 00:53:24.913
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

544
00:53:26.400 --> 00:53:29.836
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

545
00:53:31.800 --> 00:53:34.155
That way.

546
00:53:34.280 --> 00:53:37.397
You are drunk. and when
you are drunk. you forget that...

547
00:53:37.520 --> 00:53:39.317
- I am in charge!
- You are in charge.

548
00:53:39.440 --> 00:53:41.510
Fine.
Then which way do we go?

549
00:53:42.800 --> 00:53:45.030
That way!

550
00:53:46.480 --> 00:53:50.792
Oh. no!
That's the way I'm going.

551
00:53:50.920 --> 00:53:53.718
All right. all right.
You can follow me as far as the lake.

552
00:53:53.840 --> 00:53:55.876
But that's it!

553
00:53:56.000 --> 00:53:59.549
- You're not going south. are you?
- No. just as far as the lake.

554
00:53:59.720 --> 00:54:00.994
Good.

555
00:54:01.120 --> 00:54:04.590
Mumbo. Jumbo. I am hungry.
Go get me some eggs or something.

556
00:54:04.720 --> 00:54:07.188
- We are not afraid of you!
- Now!

557
00:54:13.680 --> 00:54:17.070
Kael. have you found the child?

558
00:54:18.240 --> 00:54:20.800
The search goes on. my queen.

559
00:54:20.920 --> 00:54:22.831
Why. with my powers...

560
00:54:22.960 --> 00:54:25.997
with the strength
of my great army...

561
00:54:26.120 --> 00:54:29.317
can you not find
one little child?

562
00:54:29.440 --> 00:54:31.635
We look even now.
It won't be long.

563
00:54:31.760 --> 00:54:34.957
Find the child.
Find the child!

564
00:54:35.080 --> 00:54:37.514
Time is running out.

565
00:54:45.040 --> 00:54:47.429
- Good night.
- She is kinda cute.

566
00:54:49.120 --> 00:54:50.758
When she's quiet.

567
00:54:52.160 --> 00:54:53.957
She's really a princess.

568
00:54:54.080 --> 00:54:57.709
Really?
And you're a great sorcerer.

569
00:54:57.840 --> 00:54:59.796
And I'm the king of Kashmir.

570
00:55:00.720 --> 00:55:02.915
Go to sleep. Willow.

571
00:55:03.640 --> 00:55:05.995
Good night. Madmartigan.

572
00:55:06.120 --> 00:55:08.918
Rats! Big rats! Rats!

573
00:55:09.680 --> 00:55:11.591
Rats!

574
00:55:12.320 --> 00:55:16.916
Rool. you and
that stupid rat dream!

575
00:55:25.440 --> 00:55:28.034
<i>Tuatha...</i>

576
00:55:28.160 --> 00:55:30.151
<i>lawkathok...</i>

577
00:55:30.280 --> 00:55:32.077
<i>tuatha!</i>

578
00:55:41.000 --> 00:55:43.833
- There you are.
- Madmartigan!

579
00:55:45.240 --> 00:55:47.117
'Night. Willow.

580
00:55:58.800 --> 00:56:00.631
This way! This way!

581
00:56:12.040 --> 00:56:13.837
What are you doing?

582
00:56:13.960 --> 00:56:16.190
I found some black root.
She loves it!

583
00:56:16.320 --> 00:56:19.073
Black root?
I am the father of two children...

584
00:56:19.200 --> 00:56:21.031
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

585
00:56:21.160 --> 00:56:24.197
My mother raised us
on black root.

586
00:56:24.320 --> 00:56:26.709
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

587
00:56:26.840 --> 00:56:29.400
- Doesn't it. Sticks?
- Her name is not Sticks.

588
00:56:29.520 --> 00:56:32.273
She's Elora Danan.
the future empress of Tir Asleen.

589
00:56:32.400 --> 00:56:34.595
And the last thing she's gonna want
is a hairy chest!

590
00:56:38.960 --> 00:56:42.270
Did you see what he did?
He stole our black root.

591
00:56:42.400 --> 00:56:44.356
I'll get some more.
Don't worry about it.

592
00:56:48.440 --> 00:56:50.590
There it is! The island!

593
00:56:54.200 --> 00:56:56.919
We made it.

594
00:56:57.040 --> 00:56:59.952
We have led you to the island
of the sorceress Fin Raziel.

595
00:57:00.080 --> 00:57:02.992
- We'll get a boat in that village.
- A big boat.

596
00:57:21.520 --> 00:57:25.798
- Well. looks like I got you here.
- You? What did you do?

597
00:57:25.920 --> 00:57:28.753
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs!

598
00:57:28.880 --> 00:57:32.111
- I found a boat. We're all set.
- Good.

599
00:57:32.240 --> 00:57:34.549
Take these two lizards out
and drown them.

600
00:57:34.680 --> 00:57:37.831
Lizards?
Who are you calling lizards?

601
00:57:39.880 --> 00:57:42.440
Your mother was a lizard!

602
00:57:45.320 --> 00:57:47.675
Goodbye. Sticks.

603
00:57:50.320 --> 00:57:53.039
If you really are a princess...

604
00:57:53.160 --> 00:57:55.116
take care of him.

605
00:58:02.720 --> 00:58:05.188
- Madmartigan!
- What?

606
00:58:06.160 --> 00:58:07.912
Thanks.

607
00:58:18.760 --> 00:58:21.911
- Keep walkin'. hero!
- Don't even turn around!

608
00:58:24.440 --> 00:58:26.715
It's all right. Elora.

609
00:58:26.840 --> 00:58:29.673
Go to sleep.
Nobody'll find you here.

610
00:58:29.800 --> 00:58:32.234
I'll be back with Fin Raziel
very soon.

611
00:58:32.360 --> 00:58:35.477
We will guard her
with our meagre lives.

612
00:59:02.720 --> 00:59:04.472
Raziel!

613
00:59:05.480 --> 00:59:09.109
Fin Raziel!
I have to talk to you. please!

614
00:59:20.440 --> 00:59:22.476
She's not here.

615
00:59:28.320 --> 00:59:31.710
Get back! Who are you?

616
00:59:32.800 --> 00:59:35.519
Who are you?

617
00:59:37.920 --> 00:59:40.798
- I'm Willow Ufgood.
- What are you doing here?

618
00:59:40.920 --> 00:59:44.390
I've come to find
the great sorceress Fin Raziel.

619
00:59:44.520 --> 00:59:46.954
That's me! I'm Raziel!

620
00:59:48.920 --> 00:59:50.751
This can't be right!

621
00:59:50.880 --> 00:59:54.190
One of Bavmorda's spells
transformed me.

622
00:59:56.440 --> 00:59:58.874
Believe me.
it could have been worse!

623
01:00:00.400 --> 01:00:04.518
Well. this wand is for you.
It's from Cherlindrea.

624
01:00:04.640 --> 01:00:06.710
Then the prophecy is true.

625
01:00:06.840 --> 01:00:10.196
The princess has been born.
Take me to her.

626
01:00:14.040 --> 01:00:17.157
It is Elora Danan.
Isn't she beautiful?

627
01:00:18.960 --> 01:00:21.758
Isn't she beautiful?

628
01:00:21.880 --> 01:00:24.474
- That's Raziel?
- I don't know.

629
01:00:24.600 --> 01:00:27.353
I expected something
more grand. Less...

630
01:00:27.480 --> 01:00:29.357
- Fuzzy.
- Fuzzy.

631
01:00:29.480 --> 01:00:33.075
You must use the wand.
Turn me back into my human form.

632
01:00:33.200 --> 01:00:36.351
- What do I do?
- You mean you're not a sorcerer?

633
01:00:37.640 --> 01:00:39.949
Yes. Sorta.

634
01:00:40.080 --> 01:00:41.354
I'm a farmer.

635
01:00:42.600 --> 01:00:45.160
- But I do know a few tricks.
- Tricks?

636
01:00:45.280 --> 01:00:49.512
Cherlindrea sent <i>you?</i>
You must learn real magic.

637
01:00:51.360 --> 01:00:53.555
- Horses!
- Horses!

638
01:00:53.680 --> 01:00:55.875
Quick! Take her! Hurry!

639
01:01:04.560 --> 01:01:07.358
I knew he was a traitor!

640
01:01:09.920 --> 01:01:12.354
- Sorry about this. peck.
- Keep your mouth shut.

641
01:01:13.600 --> 01:01:16.068
I told you we'd find them
without your help.

642
01:01:16.200 --> 01:01:18.077
- Give me that baby!
- No!

643
01:01:21.440 --> 01:01:25.194
- Give her back!
- Leave me alone! Don't touch me!

644
01:01:30.920 --> 01:01:32.672
This is the one
we're looking for.

645
01:01:32.800 --> 01:01:34.756
We must take it back
to Nockmaar.

646
01:01:38.720 --> 01:01:40.517
Lose your skirt?

647
01:01:48.360 --> 01:01:51.238
- I've still got what counts.
- Not for long.

648
01:01:57.640 --> 01:02:00.029
- Bring him.
- Over here!

649
01:02:18.040 --> 01:02:20.395
We'll never keep up
with those horses.

650
01:02:21.120 --> 01:02:24.032
- Then we will have to track them.
- That would take forever.

651
01:02:24.160 --> 01:02:26.628
Besides. even if we find them.
they'll catch us...

652
01:02:26.760 --> 01:02:29.797
stick us in cages. torture us
and finally devour us.

653
01:02:29.920 --> 01:02:31.717
Are you suggesting we go home?

654
01:02:31.840 --> 01:02:34.479
- Nah. This is more fun.
- All right.

655
01:02:34.600 --> 01:02:36.477
Fine. then.
Come on.

656
01:02:49.840 --> 01:02:53.071
I'm worried about Elora.
She doesn't sound good.

657
01:02:53.200 --> 01:02:55.794
Hurry! Practise
the chant I taught you!

658
01:02:56.880 --> 01:02:59.348
<i>Tanna looatha...</i>

659
01:02:59.480 --> 01:03:01.436
I can't remember
the middle part.

660
01:03:01.560 --> 01:03:03.437
<i>Locktwaar!</i>

661
01:03:03.560 --> 01:03:06.438
That's the word
that pleads for change.

662
01:03:06.560 --> 01:03:08.437
<i>Locktwaar.</i>

663
01:03:11.920 --> 01:03:14.878
Elora's cold and hungry.
She knows me.

664
01:03:15.000 --> 01:03:16.831
Please. let me take care of her.

665
01:03:16.960 --> 01:03:18.951
I don't need help from a peck.

666
01:03:23.360 --> 01:03:26.318
- What are you staring at?
- Your leg.

667
01:03:27.440 --> 01:03:29.351
I'd like to break it.

668
01:03:29.480 --> 01:03:31.357
You may find that difficult.
slave...

669
01:03:31.480 --> 01:03:33.516
while I'm up here
and you're down there.

670
01:03:36.520 --> 01:03:38.636
I hate that woman.

671
01:04:15.640 --> 01:04:17.596
I found it. Kael.

672
01:04:19.960 --> 01:04:22.269
That should make
my mother happy.

673
01:04:22.400 --> 01:04:24.277
What are they gonna do to her?

674
01:04:37.320 --> 01:04:39.834
<i>Hither walha...</i>

675
01:04:39.960 --> 01:04:43.270
<i>bairn deru bordak...</i>

676
01:04:43.400 --> 01:04:44.674
<i>bellanockt.</i>

677
01:04:46.160 --> 01:04:48.037
That's magic?
Smells terrible.

678
01:04:48.160 --> 01:04:51.197
- It's the life spark. It forms after...
- It stinks!

679
01:04:51.320 --> 01:04:54.312
- This whole thing stinks!
- Ignore him. Willow.

680
01:04:54.440 --> 01:04:57.318
- He's a fool!
- If only I had a sword!

681
01:04:58.440 --> 01:05:00.351
If only you'd quit
talking about it.

682
01:05:00.480 --> 01:05:03.631
Willow. you must transform me
to my human self.

683
01:05:03.760 --> 01:05:06.433
But. Raziel. I'm not ready yet.

684
01:05:06.560 --> 01:05:09.597
You'd better be.
Get me down.

685
01:05:13.120 --> 01:05:14.394
Ow!

686
01:05:17.920 --> 01:05:20.798
Why don't you help me get out of here
instead of chattering with that muskrat?

687
01:05:20.920 --> 01:05:22.035
Muskrat!

688
01:05:22.160 --> 01:05:26.597
When I change back to my former self.
I will crush this army...

689
01:05:26.720 --> 01:05:29.996
and take Elora Danan
to Tir Asleen...

690
01:05:30.120 --> 01:05:32.554
where she will be safe.

691
01:05:33.360 --> 01:05:36.796
Ow! What'd you bite me for?

692
01:05:36.920 --> 01:05:40.037
You need three drops of your blood
to put in the potion.

693
01:05:40.160 --> 01:05:41.798
You could've warned me.

694
01:05:43.400 --> 01:05:45.675
For beginners.
there's some pain...

695
01:05:45.800 --> 01:05:50.635
but don't let anything
break your concentration.

696
01:05:55.600 --> 01:05:58.319
<i>Hither greenan bairn</i>
<i>claideb lunanockt.</i>

697
01:05:58.440 --> 01:06:01.955
- Hello. everybody! We have arrived!
- You are saved.

698
01:06:02.960 --> 01:06:04.757
Don't interrupt.

699
01:06:06.200 --> 01:06:09.192
<i>Hither greenan bairn</i>
<i>claideb lunanockt.</i>

700
01:06:10.000 --> 01:06:11.991
What will you look like
if this works?

701
01:06:12.120 --> 01:06:14.475
- Don't interrupt.
- Sorry.

702
01:06:14.600 --> 01:06:16.397
<i>Hither greenan bairn</i>
<i>claideb lunanockt.</i>

703
01:06:16.520 --> 01:06:19.637
I am a young. beautiful woman.

704
01:06:19.760 --> 01:06:21.432
Concentrate. Willow.

705
01:06:21.560 --> 01:06:23.596
<i>Hither greenan bairn</i>
<i>claideb lunanockt.</i>

706
01:06:26.080 --> 01:06:28.071
You're losing me!

707
01:06:29.200 --> 01:06:31.430
<i>Hither greenan bairn</i>
<i>claideb lunanockt.</i>

708
01:06:36.840 --> 01:06:38.956
You all right?
Nice try. Willow.

709
01:06:46.880 --> 01:06:50.589
Farmers!
Cherlindrea sends me farmers!

710
01:06:51.720 --> 01:06:54.029
The Nelwyn
really butchered that one.

711
01:06:54.160 --> 01:06:55.912
I'm sorry. Raziel.

712
01:06:56.120 --> 01:06:57.519
You want out?

713
01:06:57.640 --> 01:07:00.108
Easy. We can pick a lock.
Come on.

714
01:07:00.240 --> 01:07:01.878
No. No. no.
Like this!

715
01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:03.956
I know what I'm doing.
It's my spear. Leave it alone.

716
01:07:04.080 --> 01:07:06.310
Let me do it.

717
01:07:06.440 --> 01:07:08.237
Out of the way. rodents.

718
01:07:09.480 --> 01:07:10.549
Take your hand off that.

719
01:07:10.680 --> 01:07:14.878
You leave that alone.
you stupid. fat Daikini!

720
01:07:17.480 --> 01:07:19.710
Dust of broken hearts.

721
01:07:30.600 --> 01:07:32.272
You are free!

722
01:07:32.400 --> 01:07:33.469
Come on. Madmartigan.

723
01:07:33.600 --> 01:07:35.795
Let's get Elora Danan
out of here.

724
01:07:35.920 --> 01:07:37.672
Yeah.

725
01:07:37.800 --> 01:07:39.836
- It'll be fun.
- Come on.

726
01:07:51.680 --> 01:07:53.557
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

727
01:07:55.040 --> 01:07:57.031
I feel good.

728
01:07:57.160 --> 01:07:59.071
The dust of broken hearts.

729
01:08:00.640 --> 01:08:01.993
Come on!

730
01:08:08.320 --> 01:08:11.232
- Let me see!
- Let <i>me</i> see. You always see.

731
01:08:11.360 --> 01:08:13.669
There's Elora. right there.
on those furs.

732
01:08:16.040 --> 01:08:19.396
Hey. wait! Leave this to us.
It's too dangerous for you.

733
01:08:19.520 --> 01:08:23.513
Only one of us should go in there.
I know what I'm doing.

734
01:08:53.240 --> 01:08:55.754
Wait. No. no!

735
01:09:06.480 --> 01:09:09.153
- I love you.
- Madmartigan!

736
01:09:09.280 --> 01:09:12.078
What are you doing?
Get the baby!

737
01:09:12.200 --> 01:09:13.474
Come on!

738
01:09:28.360 --> 01:09:30.316
Wake from this hateful sleep.

739
01:09:30.440 --> 01:09:32.670
It deprives me of your beauty.

740
01:09:34.040 --> 01:09:37.316
- The beauty of your eyes...
- One move. jackass...

741
01:09:37.440 --> 01:09:40.159
and you really will be a woman.

742
01:09:40.280 --> 01:09:45.798
You are my sun! My moon!
My starlit sky.

743
01:09:45.920 --> 01:09:49.435
Without you. I dwell in darkness.
I love you.

744
01:09:50.920 --> 01:09:52.353
What are you doing here?

745
01:09:52.480 --> 01:09:55.631
Your power has enchanted me.
I stand helpless against it.

746
01:09:55.760 --> 01:09:57.557
Come to me now.

747
01:09:57.680 --> 01:09:59.989
Tonight. let me worship you
in my arms.

748
01:10:00.120 --> 01:10:02.680
- Get away from me!
- I love you!

749
01:10:02.800 --> 01:10:05.109
Stop saying that!

750
01:10:05.240 --> 01:10:09.279
How can I stop the beating of my heart?
It pounds like never before.

751
01:10:09.400 --> 01:10:11.834
- Out of fear.
- Out of love!

752
01:10:11.960 --> 01:10:14.315
I can stop it.
I'll kill you.

753
01:10:14.440 --> 01:10:16.396
Death. next to love.
is a trivial thing.

754
01:10:19.920 --> 01:10:22.275
Your touch is worth 100.000 deaths.

755
01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:28.479
What goes on here?

756
01:10:33.400 --> 01:10:35.277
Deceiver!

757
01:10:36.840 --> 01:10:38.558
Stop him!

758
01:10:47.200 --> 01:10:49.668
Get me out!

759
01:10:59.720 --> 01:11:01.676
You <i>are</i> great!

760
01:11:04.680 --> 01:11:06.272
Get on that shield!

761
01:11:22.920 --> 01:11:24.797
After them!

762
01:11:37.680 --> 01:11:38.999
They're getting away!

763
01:11:47.920 --> 01:11:49.990
- Follow me. Rool.
- Where are you?

764
01:11:50.120 --> 01:11:51.758
I don't know.

765
01:11:52.840 --> 01:11:54.717
Oh. no!
Where did everybody go?

766
01:11:54.840 --> 01:11:56.717
Maybe it was something we said.

767
01:13:32.400 --> 01:13:34.277
What the hell happened up there?

768
01:13:34.400 --> 01:13:36.356
You started spouting poetry.

769
01:13:36.480 --> 01:13:38.914
- Poetry?
- Yeah.

770
01:13:39.040 --> 01:13:41.998
"I love you. Sorsha.
I worship you. Sorsha."

771
01:13:42.120 --> 01:13:44.031
You almost got us killed!

772
01:13:44.160 --> 01:13:45.912
"I love you. Sorsha"?

773
01:13:46.040 --> 01:13:48.315
I don't love her.
She kicked me in the face.

774
01:13:48.440 --> 01:13:50.874
I hate her! Don't I?

775
01:13:53.840 --> 01:13:56.115
Kael! Kael!

776
01:13:56.240 --> 01:13:57.798
Nockmaar soldiers!

777
01:14:00.720 --> 01:14:02.756
Hide! Get the children!
Come on!

778
01:14:05.680 --> 01:14:07.910
- Hide! Get the children!
- They're after us!

779
01:14:08.040 --> 01:14:11.510
- We need a place to hide.
- Come on. Follow me. Quick!

780
01:14:27.400 --> 01:14:30.039
I knew you'd get out
of that rattrap.

781
01:14:32.440 --> 01:14:34.317
You left me to die. Airk.

782
01:14:34.440 --> 01:14:37.512
I probably saved your life.
We were slaughtered. and I lost a lot...

783
01:14:37.640 --> 01:14:38.516
Quiet!

784
01:14:41.000 --> 01:14:42.797
Tear this village apart!

785
01:14:43.520 --> 01:14:45.795
Look everywhere!

786
01:14:45.920 --> 01:14:47.069
Find the child!

787
01:15:21.480 --> 01:15:24.313
Tell Sorsha
I search the north bank!

788
01:15:24.440 --> 01:15:25.589
Yes. General.

789
01:15:38.880 --> 01:15:40.791
Quiet!

790
01:15:59.440 --> 01:16:02.273
- Sorsha!
- Back.

791
01:16:02.880 --> 01:16:03.949
Back!

792
01:16:10.440 --> 01:16:11.668
Back.

793
01:16:13.400 --> 01:16:16.278
- Keep the baby quiet.
- She needs to be changed.

794
01:16:17.080 --> 01:16:18.832
- Nockmaar scum!
- You'll never defeat us.

795
01:16:18.960 --> 01:16:20.552
- Give up the baby!
- Shut up!

796
01:16:22.560 --> 01:16:25.870
- Why does Bavmorda want this baby?
- She's a princess.

797
01:16:26.000 --> 01:16:28.560
- We're taking her to Tir Asleen.
- Tir Asleen?

798
01:16:28.680 --> 01:16:30.557
Even if you could find it. peck...

799
01:16:30.680 --> 01:16:32.910
she's right... you'd never
get past the Nockmaar army.

800
01:16:33.040 --> 01:16:36.715
There's an even bigger army
at Tir Asleen. if we can get there.

801
01:16:41.160 --> 01:16:43.754
I've lost more than half my men
fighting Bavmorda.

802
01:16:43.880 --> 01:16:45.757
Now you and this peck
are gonna take her on?

803
01:16:46.880 --> 01:16:49.474
You always told me you served
no one. Madmartigan.

804
01:16:49.600 --> 01:16:51.477
Since when are you a crusader?

805
01:16:53.680 --> 01:16:55.636
He's not gonna help you. peck.

806
01:16:56.880 --> 01:16:59.030
He's a worthless thief.

807
01:17:00.120 --> 01:17:02.429
I'm not a thief. Airk.

808
01:17:02.560 --> 01:17:04.073
He's not a thief.

809
01:17:06.560 --> 01:17:07.549
Are you?

810
01:17:21.560 --> 01:17:23.835
I serve the Nelwyn. Airk.

811
01:17:29.720 --> 01:17:32.188
- Want to come with us?
- You'll never make it.

812
01:17:34.120 --> 01:17:36.350
Then once again
we say goodbye.

813
01:17:49.200 --> 01:17:52.431
- Over here!
- Sorsha!

814
01:17:52.560 --> 01:17:54.710
Weapons down or she's dead!

815
01:18:08.720 --> 01:18:10.597
Get to your horses!
After them!

816
01:18:54.920 --> 01:18:57.275
This way!
This way!

817
01:18:57.400 --> 01:18:59.960
As the crow flies. you fools!

818
01:19:06.600 --> 01:19:09.273
- You're holding me too tight!
- I don't want you to get away.

819
01:19:09.400 --> 01:19:13.279
Why? Because I'm your sun.
your moon. your starlit sky?

820
01:19:15.560 --> 01:19:17.516
Get your hair out of my face
or I'll chop it off.

821
01:19:21.400 --> 01:19:23.038
Did I really...

822
01:19:23.160 --> 01:19:25.116
Did I really say
those things last night?

823
01:19:25.240 --> 01:19:28.198
- In your tent?
- You said you loved me.

824
01:19:28.320 --> 01:19:30.675
- I don't remember that.
- You lied to me!

825
01:19:30.800 --> 01:19:31.915
No. I...

826
01:19:33.160 --> 01:19:35.435
I just wasn't myself last night.

827
01:19:35.560 --> 01:19:39.030
I suppose my power enchanted you
and you were helpless against it.

828
01:19:40.320 --> 01:19:42.390
- Sort of.
- Then what?

829
01:19:43.520 --> 01:19:46.671
- It went away.
- Went away?

830
01:19:46.800 --> 01:19:49.598
"I dwell in darkness without you."
and it went away?

831
01:19:49.720 --> 01:19:51.358
Yeah.

832
01:20:12.080 --> 01:20:13.832
Hurry! Kael's coming!

833
01:20:18.240 --> 01:20:20.390
Madmartigan. come on! Now!

834
01:20:28.120 --> 01:20:29.838
Madmartigan. come on!

835
01:20:31.640 --> 01:20:34.279
They're coming! Away!

836
01:20:34.400 --> 01:20:35.515
Go on!

837
01:20:52.920 --> 01:20:54.399
Whoa! Whoa!

838
01:20:55.960 --> 01:20:57.393
This way!

839
01:21:03.320 --> 01:21:06.949
Tir Asleen!
At last. Tir Asleen!

840
01:21:17.440 --> 01:21:18.714
Hello?

841
01:21:20.600 --> 01:21:22.079
Hello?

842
01:21:26.080 --> 01:21:27.399
Hello?

843
01:21:29.240 --> 01:21:31.754
Why did I listen to you. peck?

844
01:21:31.880 --> 01:21:35.190
"Everything will be all right
once we get to Tir Asleen."

845
01:21:36.080 --> 01:21:38.799
The only army around is the one that's
about to ride across this valley...

846
01:21:38.920 --> 01:21:40.672
and wipe us out!

847
01:21:40.800 --> 01:21:43.678
But Cherlindrea said
we'd be safe here.

848
01:21:44.440 --> 01:21:47.352
Safe? Look at these people.

849
01:21:47.480 --> 01:21:51.189
This place is cursed. peck.
It's falling apart. Open your eyes!

850
01:21:51.320 --> 01:21:52.594
And it...

851
01:21:54.880 --> 01:21:56.791
Trolls.

852
01:21:59.720 --> 01:22:01.676
I hate trolls.

853
01:22:02.440 --> 01:22:04.715
This is the work of Bavmorda.

854
01:22:13.560 --> 01:22:15.994
Willow? The wand.

855
01:22:16.120 --> 01:22:19.317
- Turn me back into my human form.
- Are you sure?

856
01:22:36.840 --> 01:22:37.909
Good.

857
01:22:45.200 --> 01:22:47.156
Hurry. Willow.
Transform me.

858
01:22:47.280 --> 01:22:50.078
I can't do it.
I'm just not a sorcerer.

859
01:22:50.200 --> 01:22:55.797
But you can be.
Speak and be one with the words.

860
01:22:55.920 --> 01:22:58.912
<i>Avalorium greenan...</i>

861
01:22:59.440 --> 01:23:02.193
<i>luatha tye...</i>

862
01:23:02.320 --> 01:23:04.914
Oh. Willow. you're losing me.

863
01:23:09.040 --> 01:23:11.190
Madmartigan. Kael's coming!

864
01:23:11.320 --> 01:23:15.438
- Willow. you idiot.
- Raziel?

865
01:23:16.360 --> 01:23:18.749
Arm that catapult up there.

866
01:23:39.520 --> 01:23:43.069
Good work. Madmartigan.

867
01:23:43.200 --> 01:23:44.792
What happened to you?

868
01:23:44.920 --> 01:23:47.388
Assault!
Sorsha. battering ram!

869
01:23:52.400 --> 01:23:53.799
Cut it down!

870
01:24:05.360 --> 01:24:06.315
Faster!

871
01:24:21.240 --> 01:24:23.435
Forward! Break it down!

872
01:24:43.200 --> 01:24:45.589
Again! Again!

873
01:24:50.080 --> 01:24:52.389
Willow. use the wand
on that troll.

874
01:24:54.600 --> 01:24:55.919
<i>Bellalockt!</i>

875
01:25:18.160 --> 01:25:21.470
Break it down! Forward!

876
01:26:06.760 --> 01:26:09.035
Get him!

877
01:26:30.000 --> 01:26:31.558
The other side!

878
01:26:45.640 --> 01:26:47.790
Destroy the beast!
Find the baby!

879
01:26:48.840 --> 01:26:50.432
Take that!

880
01:28:22.680 --> 01:28:25.274
Madmartigan. help!

881
01:28:36.160 --> 01:28:37.832
Get him. Madmartigan!

882
01:28:47.720 --> 01:28:49.153
Here.

883
01:29:05.040 --> 01:29:06.268
The baby!

884
01:30:05.640 --> 01:30:08.632
Airk's army. Get Kael!

885
01:30:08.760 --> 01:30:10.990
Airk's army!

886
01:30:13.400 --> 01:30:15.436
- We are here!
- You are rescued!

887
01:30:15.560 --> 01:30:18.358
- Charge!
- Charge!

888
01:30:34.640 --> 01:30:36.870
No mercy!

889
01:30:49.800 --> 01:30:51.552
Elora!

890
01:30:52.800 --> 01:30:53.915
Willow!

891
01:31:00.120 --> 01:31:01.997
- Elora's gone.
- Willow.

892
01:31:03.120 --> 01:31:05.998
They've taken her.
There were too many of them.

893
01:31:11.120 --> 01:31:12.997
Can you ride?

894
01:31:16.120 --> 01:31:17.519
Let's ride.

895
01:31:29.480 --> 01:31:31.710
I have the child!

896
01:31:55.200 --> 01:31:57.191
We need towers
and a battering ram!

897
01:31:57.320 --> 01:32:00.278
Break out the tents!
Make camp!

898
01:32:00.400 --> 01:32:02.356
Make camp!

899
01:32:02.480 --> 01:32:04.198
We'll assault at first light.

900
01:32:17.480 --> 01:32:19.391
Where's Sorsha?

901
01:32:20.520 --> 01:32:23.193
She has turned against us.
Your Highness.

902
01:32:27.160 --> 01:32:29.469
Turned against me?

903
01:32:32.960 --> 01:32:34.951
Prepare for the ritual!

904
01:32:57.600 --> 01:32:59.795
This is not an army.

905
01:33:02.920 --> 01:33:05.434
Quick. Hide.

906
01:33:10.080 --> 01:33:12.992
Use the shelter chant.
Protect yourself.

907
01:33:13.120 --> 01:33:14.997
- Why?
- Just do it.

908
01:33:20.400 --> 01:33:24.678
- We've come for Elora Danan.
- You dare to challenge me?

909
01:33:24.800 --> 01:33:26.950
You're not warriors.

910
01:33:28.560 --> 01:33:29.834
You're pigs!

911
01:33:45.080 --> 01:33:46.798
You're all pigs!

912
01:33:48.720 --> 01:33:49.869
Pigs!

913
01:33:56.120 --> 01:33:58.918
<i>Avaggdu luatha bairn</i>
<i>off haefermore.</i>

914
01:34:07.400 --> 01:34:09.470
Sorsha!

915
01:34:10.560 --> 01:34:11.913
Mother. no!

916
01:34:14.960 --> 01:34:16.154
<i>Kothon!</i>

917
01:34:36.840 --> 01:34:40.230
<i>Avaggdu luatha bairn</i>
<i>off haefermore.</i>

918
01:34:54.320 --> 01:34:55.912
Begin the ritual.

919
01:34:56.040 --> 01:34:58.713
This baby will not destroy me.

920
01:35:03.120 --> 01:35:04.678
Come. thunder!

921
01:35:06.760 --> 01:35:08.557
Come. lightning!

922
01:35:09.360 --> 01:35:12.875
Touch this altar
with your powers.

923
01:35:35.280 --> 01:35:38.317
We've come all this way
and now Elora Danan's gonna die!

924
01:35:38.440 --> 01:35:41.193
No. we can still defeat Bavmorda.

925
01:35:41.320 --> 01:35:43.311
She's too powerful. Raziel.

926
01:35:43.440 --> 01:35:46.432
Transform me.
and I will destroy her.

927
01:35:51.600 --> 01:35:55.275
Elements of eternity.
above and below.

928
01:35:56.240 --> 01:35:59.869
Balance of essence.
fire beget snow.

929
01:36:01.360 --> 01:36:04.352
- <i>Locktwarr danalora luatha danu...</i>
- Willow...

930
01:36:04.480 --> 01:36:06.391
- believe in the words.
- <i>tuatha. tuatha...</i>

931
01:36:06.520 --> 01:36:08.590
- Concentrate.
- <i>chnox danu.</i>

932
01:36:08.720 --> 01:36:10.278
<i>Locktwarr danalora...</i>

933
01:36:10.400 --> 01:36:14.109
- <i>luatha danu tuatha. tuatha.</i>
- Oh. no!

934
01:36:21.080 --> 01:36:26.029
Don't give up. Willow!

935
01:37:05.520 --> 01:37:09.274
- Has it been so long?
- I'm sorry.

936
01:37:11.560 --> 01:37:14.870
Willow. we have work to do.

937
01:37:16.120 --> 01:37:17.792
Give me the wand.

938
01:37:18.520 --> 01:37:21.876
We must undo Bavmorda's sorcery.

939
01:37:24.640 --> 01:37:26.596
Let them in now.

940
01:37:31.160 --> 01:37:34.391
<i>Tuatha grin chnox</i>
<i>y foel famau.</i>

941
01:37:47.960 --> 01:37:50.952
Black fires
forever kindled within...

942
01:37:51.080 --> 01:37:53.230
let the second rite begin.

943
01:38:10.320 --> 01:38:11.309
Quick. inside.

944
01:38:12.280 --> 01:38:14.635
That won't breach the wall.
We can't get inside.

945
01:38:14.760 --> 01:38:17.558
- Elora Danan will die...
- Unless we save her.

946
01:38:17.680 --> 01:38:19.955
- Bavmorda's too powerful.
- No!

947
01:38:20.800 --> 01:38:25.191
She cannot transform you again.
My spell is protecting this camp.

948
01:38:25.320 --> 01:38:27.276
But can your magic
get us inside the fortress?

949
01:38:29.440 --> 01:38:31.112
We can't do it.

950
01:38:31.240 --> 01:38:32.798
Wait!

951
01:38:32.920 --> 01:38:35.832
Back home in my village.
we have a lot of gophers.

952
01:38:35.960 --> 01:38:38.190
- Willow. this is war. not agriculture.
- I know.

953
01:38:38.320 --> 01:38:41.278
But I have an idea
how to get inside the castle.

954
01:38:45.760 --> 01:38:48.638
<i>Ocht veth bordak stira.</i>

955
01:38:48.760 --> 01:38:51.228
<i>Ocht veth bordak stira.</i>

956
01:38:59.280 --> 01:39:02.158
Madmartigan. you and I are soldiers.
The peck's plan will never work.

957
01:39:03.760 --> 01:39:06.797
If the baby dies.
all hope for the future is lost.

958
01:39:09.120 --> 01:39:10.872
I'm going to fight.

959
01:39:14.240 --> 01:39:15.992
Me too.

960
01:39:23.080 --> 01:39:25.878
All right. we've got to decide
who's gonna go and who's gonna stay.

961
01:40:13.920 --> 01:40:18.596
Willow. all these years
I have waited to face Bavmorda.

962
01:40:18.720 --> 01:40:21.109
It is you
that has made this possible.

963
01:40:22.440 --> 01:40:26.479
Whatever happens.
I shall always admire you.

964
01:40:36.760 --> 01:40:38.955
Your children...

965
01:40:39.080 --> 01:40:41.640
will come to remember this day.

966
01:40:51.760 --> 01:40:54.638
We call upon you to surrender!

967
01:40:56.720 --> 01:40:58.597
We are all-powerful sorcerers.

968
01:40:59.640 --> 01:41:02.996
Give us the baby.
or we'll destroy you!

969
01:41:09.000 --> 01:41:11.389
Kill them!

970
01:41:29.880 --> 01:41:31.438
Patience. Willow.

971
01:41:33.280 --> 01:41:34.872
Courage. Willow.

972
01:41:50.320 --> 01:41:52.276
Back to the castle!

973
01:42:16.840 --> 01:42:19.957
<i>Ocht veth nockthirth bordak!</i>

974
01:42:20.080 --> 01:42:23.755
Exile the child to the 13th night.

975
01:42:31.200 --> 01:42:32.553
This way!

976
01:43:10.360 --> 01:43:16.356
<i>Nockthirth</i>
<i>plankton firth foreth forewar.</i>

977
01:43:16.480 --> 01:43:18.630
<i>Ocht veth nock!</i>

978
01:43:18.760 --> 01:43:21.149
It's all right. Willow.

979
01:43:21.280 --> 01:43:23.077
You don't have to go.

980
01:43:23.200 --> 01:43:25.873
Light the 13th candle!

981
01:43:40.240 --> 01:43:41.912
Raziel.

982
01:43:42.040 --> 01:43:43.359
Mother!

983
01:43:47.320 --> 01:43:51.598
Traitor child.
I must despise you now.

984
01:44:20.800 --> 01:44:23.678
- I won't let you kill that child.
- Away!

985
01:44:23.800 --> 01:44:25.119
<i>Avaggdu...</i>

986
01:44:26.040 --> 01:44:28.508
<i>strokt!</i>

987
01:44:44.360 --> 01:44:47.670
Your powers have gained
in strength. Raziel.

988
01:44:47.800 --> 01:44:52.715
I have Cherlindrea's wand.
Bavmorda.

989
01:44:54.920 --> 01:44:58.754
Elora Danan will be queen.

990
01:45:11.240 --> 01:45:12.389
Now you die!

991
01:45:16.640 --> 01:45:19.518
<i>Furrochk flarem!</i>

992
01:45:48.360 --> 01:45:50.510
<i>Claideb cla...</i>

993
01:45:52.160 --> 01:45:55.470
<i>Clai main!</i>
<i>Lunano ockht!</i>

994
01:45:57.400 --> 01:46:00.119
<i>Bachktu inno!</i>

995
01:47:47.400 --> 01:47:48.435
Airk!

996
01:47:51.600 --> 01:47:53.431
Win this war for me.

997
01:48:30.880 --> 01:48:32.313
Die!

998
01:50:27.000 --> 01:50:29.878
Bring back that child. peck.

999
01:50:33.920 --> 01:50:35.194
Who are you?

1000
